The paper deals with the complexity of Boolean functions, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The focus is on block sensitivity, which is a measure of the complexity of Boolean functions (cs.DS). The paper also involves group theory, which is a common tool in the study of Boolean functions (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial structures such as permutations and minterms, which are often studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves information theory, as it considers the amount of information required to compute a Boolean function (cs.IT).
